slides.title: These are the wikipedia pages about Gambling
slides.text:
Each node is a wikipedia page.
Links are HTTP links one can find in the see also category.
From "Problem gambling" to "Gaming control board".

slides.title: Internet addiction disorder
slides.text:
Close to the "Gambling addiction" cluster one can find the "Internet addiciton disorder".
Two addictions on Internet.

slides.title: A tentative to control addiction
slides.text:
"content-control software" !

Yeah well we also find "Internet censorship".

But on the right another theme starts to appear : "Pornography addiction",  "Sexaholics Anonymous"...

slides.title: This is what we labeled "addiction"
slides.text:
This green color is chosen to isolate visually the classification of the network by "human coding".

The color is defined by the attribute one node have in the "main topic" attribute.

slides.title: Now this is our complete network !
slides.text:
Eleonora Grotto from Density Design Lab who work for her master thesis created this graph.
She used the [seealsology tool from Density Design Lab](http://labs.densitydesign.org/seealsology/) which creates a network by crawling the see-also links of wikipedia pages.  

Yes she chose specific entry points manually after  field work.

slides.title: The main cluster : Gender
slides.text: The main cluster of the graph are pages about Gender issues.
